The paper discusses the development of intelligent negotiation systems using multi-agent based protocols and specialized negotiation languages, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also proposes a new framework and architecture for negotiation automation, which can be categorized under Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). The paper also discusses classical negotiation methods and architectures, which can be classified under Game Theory (cs.GT) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
